<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/27950781-j-roberto"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1502620136i/27950781._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/27950781-j-roberto">J. Roberto </a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Portnoy&apos;s Complaint was full of life from joy to depression. It was original and sex was full of passion. This Sabbath book that I could not finish is<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Portnoy's Complaint was full of life from joy to depression. It was original and sex was full of passion. This Sabbath book that I could not finish is flat and boring from the beginning and the personages uninteresting. Why he wrote this. I do not know, maybe a reflect of the declining of lust in his latter years. I remember some excellent books by P. Roth like the Professor of Desire. Sabbath is not credible in his desires. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
