<div id="review_250482352" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/250482352" />
    <a title="Dan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/870755-dan"><img alt="Dan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643916040p2/870755.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/250482352?book_show_action=true">Dec 23, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dan" href="/user/show/870755-dan">Dan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780679772590" href="/book/show/11654.Sabbath_s_Theater">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/870755-dan?shelf=2012">2012</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/870755-dan?shelf=homework-from-the-ladies">homework-from-the-ladies</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/870755-dan?shelf=christmas-2011">christmas-2011</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer250482352" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer448581564891231093">After the death of his longtime mistress, disgraced former puppeteer Mickey Sabbath sinks deeper and deeper into a prison of depression... <br/><br/>First off, Sabbath&apos;s Theater won the National Book award in 1995. It&apos;s not surprising since it was superbly written. On the other hand, it&apos;s also dirtier than a stack of used <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31142965' rel='nofollow noopener'>Longarm&apos;s.</a> Seriously. Every time I thought it couldn&apos;t get any dirtier, Sabbath did something like masturbate on his mistress&apos;s grave.<br/><br/>There really isn&apos;t much of a plot. Sabbath&apos;s mistres</span>
  <span id="freeText448581564891231093" style="display:none">After the death of his longtime mistress, disgraced former puppeteer Mickey Sabbath sinks deeper and deeper into a prison of depression... <br /><br />First off, Sabbath's Theater won the National Book award in 1995. It's not surprising since it was superbly written. On the other hand, it's also dirtier than a stack of used <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31142965" rel="nofollow noopener">Longarm's.</a> Seriously. Every time I thought it couldn't get any dirtier, Sabbath did something like masturbate on his mistress's grave.<br /><br />There really isn't much of a plot. Sabbath's mistress dies and his life comes apart, forcing him to explore his past. Good thing he has the memories of unbelievably numerous conquests to dwell on. Sabbath's such a pervert that I couldn't seem to read more than fifty pages of this at a time. I cringed when a friend took pity on him only to catch him in the process of masturbating to a picture of his college age daughter.<br /><br />There are themes and other novely things in Sabbath's Theater but it's hard to see past the river of semen to get to them. It seems to be about how people are unable to escape the prisons they create for themselves. And fornication.<br /><br />It's a testament to Philip Roth's skill as a writer that he made me feel sorry for a dirty old man like Mickey Sabbath. Actually, I don't think there's a character in this book I liked. <br /><br />I wonder if the next National Book award winner I read will have this much smut in it...<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="448581564891231093" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


