  <span id="freeText14722598052684791233" style="display:none">Non-stop, rebarbative descriptions of the sex act in a graveyard. An awful slog. For me, Roth is one of those hot or cold authors. This one left me stone cold. Hey, if you're looking for masturbatory fodder, this is your novel. I happen not to be. As an alternative I would recommended any of the following: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11650.American_Pastoral__The_American_Trilogy___1_" title="American Pastoral (The American Trilogy, #1) by Philip Roth" rel="nofollow noopener">American Pastoral</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11655.The_Counterlife" title="The Counterlife by Philip Roth" rel="nofollow noopener">The Counterlife</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50696.The_Ghost_Writer" title="The Ghost Writer by Philip Roth" rel="nofollow noopener">The Ghost Writer</a>, or <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11734.The_Human_Stain__The_American_Trilogy___3_" title="The Human Stain (The American Trilogy, #3) by Philip Roth" rel="nofollow noopener">The Human Stain</a>. Certainly the first two here are masterpieces.</span>
