<div id="review_2429912629" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2429912629" />
    <a title="d.a.v.i.d" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/67794375-d-a-v-i-d"><img alt="d.a.v.i.d" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643983104p2/67794375.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2429912629?book_show_action=true">Apr 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="d.a.v.i.d" class="user" itemprop="url" name="d.a.v.i.d" href="/user/show/67794375-d-a-v-i-d">d.a.v.i.d</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/10743014-sabbath-s-theater">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/67794375-d-a-v-i-d?shelf=philip-roth">philip-roth</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2429912629" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12503036265388267339">This may be Roth’s best work.<br/><br/>I would go further to say I believe he is one of America’s greatest writers.<br/><br/>If you despise curse words, descriptions of carnal affairs, expositions of lust, desire, and sexual needs, do not read this book. The lexicon would become more important to you then the substantive messages this book retains.<br/><br/>This is the story of Mickey Sabbath, a sixty-four-year-old man. Now an orphan as an adult. As many of us become, ineluctably.<br/><br/><br/>Absolutely brilliant.<br/><br/>Ten stars.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


