<span id="freeTextContainer12063353447711683786">Perverse and falling in places. This book is not for the faint hearted. Very descriptive passages about sex, masturbation and melancholic overtones from the main character. I think Molly Bloom from Joyce&apos;s Ulysses may have been in mind while writing this book. I think James Joyce would love to have read this. It has a certain shock factor for people who don&apos;t normally read this sort of thing. </span>
